<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Mirriana_00 on 04-22-2001 08:33 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">If mana is close, I just don't use an ac buff at all.  If I can afford it, I BoF the main tank, then enc, then secondary tanks, then myself.  Any other int/wis casters don't get it at all unless I am totally full on mana.

The other thing to think about is that the AC you are seeing is only half the story.  Apparently in Beta you got to see the damage avoidance and the damage absorption numbers.  They thought that was too confusing, so they made them into one number, but it doesn't always add up exactly.  I could be totally wrong about all this, but I have heard that it can make a difference.  Maybe BoF adds a lot more to one number and not the other, or maybe it is 30 less absorbtion and 20 more avoidance, which would be better, maybe.

It'd be interesting to see some parsed logs of a few hours of fighting with either spell cast.</TEXTAREA>
